Title: A Test for Instrument Validity 
Author-Name: Toru Kitagawa  
Abstract:
  This paper develops a specification test for instrument validity in the
 heterogeneous treatment effect model with a binary treatment and a
 discrete instrument. The strongest testable implication for instrument
 validity is given by the condition for nonnegativity of point‐identifiable
 compliers' outcome densities. Our specification test infers this testable
 implication using a variance‐weighted Kolmogorov–Smirnov test statistic.
 The test can be applied to both discrete and continuous outcome cases, and
 an extension of the test to settings with conditioning covariates is
 provided. 
